## How it works

```
Dev adds ComposeWind to project
         │
         ▼
KSP scans classpath
         │
         ├── finds androidx.compose.ui.Modifier
         ├── finds ALL extension functions on Modifier
         │   (from compose-ui, compose-foundation,
         │    compose-material3, AND any custom ones)
         │
         ▼
KSP generates CwModifierExtensions.kt
         │
         ├── .fillMaxWidth()  →  .wFull()
         ├── .padding(16.dp)  →  .p(4)
         ├── .clip(...)       →  .roundLg()
         ├── .clickable()     →  .clickable()
         └── YourCustomMod()  →  .cwYourCustomMod()
```

Custom project extensions get wrapped too — automatically. That's the killer feature.

