## The naming strategy KSP uses

KSP needs a naming rule to convert function names to CW names. Keep it simple:

```
fillMaxWidth()          →  wFull()
fillMaxHeight()         →  hFull()
fillMaxSize()           →  fill()
padding(all)            →  p(scale)
padding(horizontal)     →  px(scale)
padding(vertical)       →  py(scale)
background(color)       →  bg(color)
clip(shape)             →  round(shape)
clickable()             →  clickable()
alpha(float)            →  alpha(float)
[unknown/custom]        →  cw + PascalCase of original name
```

Unknown functions get `cw` prefix — so nothing is lost, nothing breaks, everything gets a wrapper.

